description.narrative: UNICEF continued policy design and programme support to strengthen the national child- and gender-sensitive social protection system in the country. The UNICEF cash plus pilot (ISNP) contributed to improved linkage services for 57,631 PSNP clients in three woredas and supported 436,900 people through contributions to PSNP's shock-responsive mechanisms. As a result, access to nutrition and child protection services as well as health insurance and humanitarian aid for children in pilot regions have improved. UNICEF also successfully advocated for the vertical expansion of the Urban Productive Safety Net Programme, through provision of hygiene materials and cash top-ups to respond to CVOID-19. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020
